<body>
    <h1>User Generated Content</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <div class=3D"contentLayout2">=20
<div class=3D"columnLayout two-right-sidebar" data-layout=3D"two-right-side=
bar">=20
<div class=3D"cell normal" data-type=3D"normal">=20
<div class=3D"innerCell">=20
<h1 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-Introduction">Introduction</h1>
<h2 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-ContentEdit">Content Edit</h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.2</span>=
</p>
<p>eZ Platform comes with content edition features via the Symfony stack. T=
hey are meant, in addition the PlatformUI's editing capabilities, to allow =
the implementation of User Generated Content from the frontend.</p>
<h1 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-Usage">Usage</h1>
<h2 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-Creatingacontentitemwithoutusingadraft">Crea=
ting a content item without using a draft</h2>
<p>As of eZ Platform 1.2, a new&nbsp;<code>/content/edit/nodraft</code> rou=
te is available. It will show a Content item creation form for a given Cont=
ent Type:</p>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">argument</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">type</th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">description</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>contentTypeIdentifier</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>string</code></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">The identifier of the content type to create. Ex=
ample: <code>folder</code>, <code>article</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>languageCode</code></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>string</code></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">Language code the content item mus=
t be created in. Example: <code>eng-GB</code></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>parentLocationId</code></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd"><code>integer</code></td>
<td colspan=3D"1" class=3D"confluenceTd">ID of the Location the content ite=
m must be created in. Example: <code>2</code></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<p>For now a very limited subset of Field Types is supported. These are:</p=
>
<ul>
<li><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.2</span=
><code> TextLine</code> and&nbsp;<code>TextBlock</code></li>
<li><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.4</span=
> <code>Selection</code>, <code>Checkbox</code> and <code>User</code></li>
</ul>
<p>More will be added in the near future.</p>
<h2 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-Registeringnewusers">Registering new users</=
h2>
<p><span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">V1.4</span>=
</p>
<p>You can allow your users to create accounts by employing the <code>/regi=
ster</code> route. This route leads to a registration form that, when fille=
d in, creates a new User Content item in the repository.</p>
<h4 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-UserGroups">User Groups</h4>
<p>By default, new Users generated in this way are placed in the Guest acco=
unts&nbsp;group. You can select a different default group in the following =
section of configuration:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        default:
            user_registration:
                group_id: &lt;userGroupContentId&gt;</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<h4 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-Registrationformtemplates">Registration form=
 templates</h4>
<p>You can use custom templates for the registration form and for the regis=
tration confirmation page.</p>
<p>These templates are defined with the following configuration:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        default:
            user_registration:
                templates:
                    form: 'user/registration_form.html.twig'
                    confirmation: 'user/registration_confirmation.html.twig=
'</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>with the following templates in <code><span class=3D"pl-s">app/Resources=
/views/user/registration_form.html.twig</span></code>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">{% extends noLayout is defined and noLayout =3D=3D true ? viewbaseL=
ayout : pagelayout %}
{% block content %}
     {% import "EzSystemsRepositoryFormsBundle:Content:content_form.html.tw=
ig" as contentForms %}
    =20
     &lt;section class=3D"ez-content-edit"&gt;
         {{ contentForms.display_form(form) }}
     &lt;/section&gt;
{% endblock %}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>and in <code><span class=3D"pl-s">app/Resources/views/user/registration_=
confirmation.html.twig</span></code>:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">{% extends noLayout is defined and noLayout =3D=3D true ? viewbaseL=
ayout : pagelayout %}
{% block content %}
    &lt;h1&gt;Your account has been created&lt;/h1&gt;
    &lt;p class=3D"user-register-confirmation-message"&gt;
        Thank you for registering an account. You can now &lt;a href=3D"{{ =
path('login') }}"&gt;login&lt;/a&gt;.
    &lt;/p&gt;
{% endblock %}</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"UserGeneratedContent-RepositoryForms">Repository Forms</h2>
<ul>
<li>Repository:&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://github.com/ezsystems/repository-form=
s" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://github.com/ezsystems/rep=
ository-forms</a></li>
<li>Package:&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://packagist.org/packages/ezsystems/reposi=
tory-forms" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">http://packagist.org/p=
ackages/ezsystems/repository-forms</a></li>
</ul>
<p>This package provides form-based interaction for the Repository Value ob=
jects.</p>
<p>It is currently used by:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: square;">
<li><code>ezsystems/platform-ui-bundle</code>&nbsp;for most management inte=
rfaces: Sections, Content Types, Roles, Policies, etc.</li>
<li><code>ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel</code>&nbsp;for user registration, and=
 user generated content</li>
</ul>
</div>=20
</div>=20
